[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: MIL-STD-498 SDD (Software Design Description)

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1. Scope

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.1 Identification

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-001
TITLE: Design Document Identification
STATEMENT: This document shall be identified as the Software Design Description (SDD) for the Satellite Communication Management System (SCMS), version 1.0.
RATIONALE: Proper document identification ensures configuration management and design traceability.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.2 System overview

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-002
TITLE: Design Overview
STATEMENT: The SCMS software design shall implement a microservices architecture with distributed components, secure communication protocols, and scalable infrastructure for satellite network management.
RATIONALE: Architectural overview establishes the foundation for detailed design specifications.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.3 Document overview

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-003
TITLE: Design Document Structure
STATEMENT: This document shall be organized into sections covering design overview, architectural design, detailed design, interface design, and design constraints.
RATIONALE: Structured organization facilitates design review and implementation guidance.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 2. Referenced documents

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-004
TITLE: Design References
STATEMENT: The design shall reference the SRS document, system architecture standards, security design patterns, and industry best practices for distributed systems.
RATIONALE: Design references ensure consistency with requirements and established patterns.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3. CSCI-wide design decisions

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-005
TITLE: Architecture Decision
STATEMENT: The system shall implement a microservices architecture to enable independent development, deployment, and scaling of system components.
RATIONALE: Microservices architecture provides flexibility and maintainability for complex distributed systems.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-006
TITLE: Technology Stack Decision
STATEMENT: The system shall use Python for backend services, React for frontend, PostgreSQL for data persistence, and Docker for containerization.
RATIONALE: Selected technology stack ensures security compliance, performance, and operational reliability.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-007
TITLE: Security Design Decision
STATEMENT: The system shall implement defense-in-depth security with multiple layers of protection including network, application, and data security controls.
RATIONALE: Layered security approach provides robust protection against various threat vectors.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4. CSCI architectural design

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.1 CSCI components

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-008
TITLE: Network Management Component
STATEMENT: The Network Management Component shall handle satellite configuration, routing algorithms, and real-time network monitoring with automated failover capabilities.
RATIONALE: Dedicated network management component ensures focused functionality and operational reliability.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-009
TITLE: Security Component
STATEMENT: The Security Component shall provide authentication, authorization, encryption, and intrusion detection with centralized security policy management.
RATIONALE: Centralized security component ensures consistent security controls across all system functions.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-010
TITLE: User Interface Component
STATEMENT: The User Interface Component shall provide web-based dashboards, configuration tools, and monitoring displays with role-based access control.
RATIONALE: Comprehensive user interface component enables efficient system operation and management.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-011
TITLE: Data Management Component
STATEMENT: The Data Management Component shall handle data persistence, backup, recovery, and archival with appropriate security and performance optimizations.
RATIONALE: Robust data management component ensures data integrity and operational continuity.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.2 Concept of execution

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-012
TITLE: Service Execution Model
STATEMENT: The system shall execute as containerized microservices with automatic scaling, load balancing, and health monitoring for continuous operation.
RATIONALE: Containerized execution model ensures deployment consistency and operational reliability.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-013
TITLE: Communication Model
STATEMENT: Services shall communicate via RESTful APIs and message queues with secure authentication and encrypted data transmission.
RATIONALE: Secure communication model ensures system integrity and data protection.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.3 Interface design

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.3.1 Interface identification and diagrams

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-014
TITLE: External API Interface
STATEMENT: The system shall provide RESTful API interfaces for satellite control, network management, and system integration with OAuth 2.0 authentication.
RATIONALE: Standardized external interfaces enable system integration and automation capabilities.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-015
TITLE: Internal Service Interface
STATEMENT: Internal services shall communicate via well-defined APIs with consistent error handling, data formats, and security protocols.
RATIONALE: Consistent internal interfaces facilitate service development and system maintenance.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-016
TITLE: Database Interface
STATEMENT: The system shall interface with PostgreSQL databases using connection pooling, prepared statements, and transaction management for data integrity.
RATIONALE: Robust database interface ensures reliable data persistence and performance.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5. Software unit detailed design

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-017
TITLE: Authentication Module
STATEMENT: The Authentication Module shall implement multi-factor authentication, session management, and secure token handling with automatic timeout and logout capabilities.
RATIONALE: Comprehensive authentication module ensures system security and user accountability.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-018
TITLE: Routing Engine
STATEMENT: The Routing Engine shall implement intelligent traffic routing algorithms with load balancing, failover logic, and priority-based traffic management.
RATIONALE: Advanced routing engine optimizes network utilization and ensures reliable communication.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-019
TITLE: Monitoring Agent
STATEMENT: The Monitoring Agent shall collect system metrics, generate alerts, and provide real-time status updates with configurable thresholds and notification rules.
RATIONALE: Comprehensive monitoring agent enables proactive system management and rapid incident response.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-020
TITLE: Configuration Manager
STATEMENT: The Configuration Manager shall handle dynamic configuration updates, version control, and deployment management with rollback capabilities.
RATIONALE: Robust configuration manager ensures system adaptability and operational stability.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 6. Requirements traceability

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-021
TITLE: Design Traceability
STATEMENT: All design elements shall be traceable to software requirements through a comprehensive traceability matrix linking components, modules, and requirements.
RATIONALE: Requirements traceability ensures complete requirement coverage and facilitates change impact analysis.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 7. Notes

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SDD-022
TITLE: Design Notes
STATEMENT: This design document shall be maintained under configuration control with version history and change tracking to ensure design consistency and traceability.
RATIONALE: Document maintenance ensures design accuracy and stakeholder communication.

[/SECTION]
